news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM directs officials to accelerate development projects
news.para: During a review meeting held here, Adityanath assessed the progress of projects across key departments, including Gorakhpur Development Authority (GDA), Municipal Corporation, Public Works Department, Irrigation Department, Jal Nigam, and Gorakhpur Industrial Development Authority (GIDA).

news.title: Registration of properties in Hyderabad up 7% to 76,613 units in 2024: Knight Frank
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India said the total value of properties registered increased 23 per cent to Rs 47,173 crore during 2024 from Rs 38,395 crore in the preceding year.

news.title: Gujarat CM allocates Rs 605.48 crore for urban development projects
news.para: The CM has prioritized the provision of essential physical infrastructure facilities such as water, electricity, sewerage, and roads for citizens.

news.title: HMDA plans to raise Rs 20,000 crore for infrastructure projects in Hyderabad
news.para: The authority recently invited expressions of interest (EOI) to appoint an advisor-cum-merchant banker to facilitate the process within 18 months, extendable by a year if necessary.

news.title: Property deals remain slow in Purandar despite Maharashtra govt’s push for airport
news.para: Official data shows 3,602 sale documents were registered last year, which was a marginal rise from 3,315 recorded in 2023.

news.title: Residents of Somayampalayam village oppose merger with Coimbatore civic body
news.para: ​​The merger, they argued, would deprive them of central government funds, welfare programmes, and livelihood opportunities, severely affecting their lives.

news.title: Goa police bust multi-crore fake villa scam, four held
news.para: Police arrested four persons from Hyderabad and Jaipur. Initial police investigation has revealed that over 500 people were duped by the fraudsters to the tune of crores of rupees, said North Goa SP Akshat Kaushal.

news.title: Former vacant land tenants in Dharavi included in redevelopment project: Official
news.para: No one from Dharavi will be rendered homeless under this scheme as every tenement holder is going to get a home of their dreams," said SVR Srinivas, CEO, DRP/SRA.

news.title: Gurugram administration cracks down on illegal gates in residential colonies
news.para: The action came after a meeting chaired by the DC, where it was revealed that several RWAs violated permissions by erecting gates instead of boom barriers, obstructing public access and posing serious challenges during emergencies.

news.title: Only 70 lakh women in 7.1 crore workers employed in Indian real estate: Report
news.para: "With approximately 71 million workers employed in the sector, only 7 million are women, resulting in a Female Labour Force Participation Rate (LFPR) of 25.1 per cent," the report said.

news.title: About 95% of sanctioned PMAY-U houses completed in Uttar Pradesh: Minister
news.para: "The scheme has also promoted economic equality, enabling people from all sections of society to own their homes and live together," the Urban development minister AK Sharma said.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRC cancels tender for Nariman Point land development after RBI's request
news.para: ​​The release said MMRC had issued a Request for Proposal (RFP) for property development at this premium location via the CPPP Portal on October 3, 2024.

news.title: CBIC removes 18% GST on rent from property owners not registered under GST
news.para: The GST department previously introduced new regulations regarding GST liability for leased commercial properties, effective from Oct 10, 2024.

news.title: Ratings agencies downgrade China Vanke on deepening property sector woes
news.para: Both rating agencies slashed Vanke's ratings by two notches to 'B-' from 'B+', citing the company's eroding financial flexibility and an uncertain sales outlook for 2025.

news.title: Aurum PropTech's net loss narrows to Rs 8.52 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Aurum PropTech has reported a growth of 13.11 per cent in its net consolidated total income during the quarter ending December 31, 2024. It had registered total income of Rs 70.23 crore in Q3 FY25 as against Rs 62.09 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Hong Kong's New World Development denies debt restructuring talks
news.para: New World has the highest debt among its Hong Kong peers at HK$199 billion ($25.57 billion), JPMorgan data showed in July, and the company has hastened the sale of its assets to raise funds.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's net profit rises 71.70% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Oberoi Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,460.27 crore, a growth of 34.85 per cent from Rs 1,082.85 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty posts net profit of Rs 42.52 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 174.76 crore, a growth of 186.59 per cent from Rs 60.98 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Survey for housing scheme PMAY-Rural to begin in Odisha on January 24: Minister
news.para: "Eligible persons can also apply to get a house under PMAY. They can apply in both online and offline mode. A portal would also be launched for this purpose," he said.
